The Oviorie Community Vigilante in Ethiope-East Local Government Area of Delta State, on Sunday morning gunned down four suspected armed robbery suspects, DAILY POST can report. The suspects had terrorized Oviorie Community and its environs before they met their waterloo. Found in the possession of the deceased suspects were cut-to-size guns and other sophisticated weapons. The suspects were gunned down by the vigilante led by Chief Sunday Akpobi A.k.a, Escobar during a robbery operation in the community. When contacted for comments, the Delta State Commissioner of Police, CP Mohammed Hafiz Inuwa confirmed the report in a text message he sent to Our Correspondent in Warri. Details laterâ€¦..